              </p>

              <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

              <h3>What is the Colorado state sales tax rate?</h3>
              <p>
                The base Colorado state sales tax rate is <strong>2.9%</strong>.
                Local governments can add their own sales taxes on top of this
                rate.
              </p>

              <h3>How do I find the correct local rate for my address?</h3>
              <p>
                You typically need to use an official rate lookup tool (often
                provided by the Colorado Department of Revenue or certified
                vendors) that uses the delivery address or location of the sale.
                Once you know the component rates, you can plug them into this
                calculator.
              </p>

              <h3>Are groceries taxed in Colorado?</h3>
              <p>
                Most food for home consumption is exempt from the
                <strong>state</strong> 2.9% sales tax, but some local
